Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with private information retrieval (PIR) which is a topic in information theory. 
2. cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses a distributed storage system and proposes a new PIR scheme for it. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - PIR is a cryptographic technique used to protect the privacy of users accessing data from a server. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper may involve discussions on the computational complexity of the proposed PIR scheme. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper may involve discussions on the use of PIR in social and information networks.
